## ğŸ¤” What is ACM?

The **Android Configuration Manager (ACM)** was a lightweight library designed to simplify app configuration storage in Android. Instead of dealing with complex **SQLite**, **Shared Preferences**, or **file-based persistence**, ACM allowed developers to **store configuration settings as Java objects** â€“ a sort of **Light Object Mapping (LOM)** for Android. âœ¨

## ğŸ¯ Key Features

âœ… **Android Backup Support** â€“ Integrated with Shared Preferences ğŸ”„
âœ… **Saves Time** â€“ Reduces boilerplate for persisting objects â³
âœ… **Future-Proof** â€“ Fault-tolerant handling of unexpected changes ğŸ› ï¸
âœ… **Uses Objects** â€“ No more error-prone key-value pairs! ğŸ·ï¸
âœ… **Polymorphism-Friendly** â€“ Works with parent-child config structures ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ‘©â€ğŸ‘¦â€ğŸ‘¦

## ğŸš€ Quick Start

```java
// Define your configuration class
MyConfig config = new MyConfig();
config.setId("MyConfig");
config.setMyBoolean(true);

// Grab Android SharedPreferences
SharedPreferences sharedPreferences =
    PreferenceManager.getDefaultSharedPreferences(getApplicationContext());
ConfigManager configManager = new ConfigManager(sharedPreferences);

// Setup a deserializer
SharedPrefenceConfigDeserialiser deserialiser =
    new SharedPrefenceConfigDeserialiser(sharedPreferences, config);
configManager.add(new DefaultConfigDeserializerStrategy(deserialiser));

// Save and retrieve the config
configManager.saveConfig(config);
MyConfig persistedConfig = (MyConfig) configManager.getConfig("MyConfig");

// Print stored value
System.out.println(persistedConfig.getMyBoolean());
```

## ğŸ—ï¸ ACM Components

- **`ConfigManager`** â€“ The main entry point for saving/loading configs ğŸ”„
- **`ConfigListActivity`** â€“ Manages a list of config objects ğŸ“‹
- **`GenericPreferenceActivity`** â€“ Handles single config objects âš™ï¸
- **`PreferenceLauncherActivity`** â€“ Launches config activities ğŸš€

## ğŸ¬ Example: NZBAir Integration

ACM was widely used in apps like **NZBAir**, where:

ğŸ“Œ *Preference Launcher* provided an entry point to different configuration types.
ğŸ“Œ *Preference List Activity* managed multiple provider configurations.
ğŸ“Œ *Config Activity* generated UI forms for configuration objects automatically.

